"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Neat attempt, but quite buggy.</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 из 5 звезд\" data-title-template=\"%s из 5 звезд\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/modparlor\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f81b79533c4c6aaf044543e0e0242bf8?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f81b79533c4c6aaf044543e0e0242bf8?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/modparlor\" class=\"reviewer-name\">modparlor</a> <span class=\"review-date\">Август 29, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I just got the Pro Version for an online presence. I expected this tool to save me work over integrating ChartJS myself and entering the data manually into the JS arrays. I\'m slowing regreting my purchase as I edit this buglist for the 5th time. Bugs dimish the experience, some bugs are *really* annoying/bad.\n\nThese bugs have shown up whilst working with columcharts:\n\n- Whenever I dublicate a Chart with the ChartJS API it clones the chart but sets the Google API as default. Resulting in making some adjustments such as tick setting impossible. I have yet to find a way to change the API after a chart has been created.\n\n- Each Chart with manual data has \"Array\" as a title\n\n- Manual data doesn\'t save unless you refresh the chart view in edit mode. Hit \"Save Chart\", see overview with no changes, all work gone ... super annoying\n\n- Cloned Charts with invisible legends have their legends visible again\n\n- Text is squished in columcharts when loading them for editing\n\n- Column colors change randomly when switching between data editor and chart view. The fun part: The last new colors are automaticaly saved even though I didn\'t save them. ... WTF?\n\nMissing feature:\n- Still havent found a way to color colums individually. With the \"random surprise color\" bug from above this makes any sort of coloring an adventure and an excercise in praying and hoping.\n\n\nConclusion:\nThis still needs some serious work. This is a release candidate at best, not a finished product. Very frustrating.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Fantastic!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 из 5 звезд\" data-title-template=\"%s из 5 звезд\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/raquelordonez\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/909270d0fbe59904b1ca79f557e6dcec?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/909270d0fbe59904b1ca79f557e6dcec?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/raquelordonez\" class=\"reviewer-name\">raquelordonez</a> <span class=\"re