g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/shimunto\" class=\"reviewer-name\">shimunto</a> <span class=\"review-date\">Июль 9, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">its mass my home page view and after deactivate my website look grate again.... \n\nMy site WordPress 5.2.2 running with Online Shop theme.\n\nEdited: good support team will help me to reactive this plugin again on my site. Surely you deserve 5 star.\n\nTHANKS A LOT @jamesosborne</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">AMP ERRORS ON CONSOLE</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 из 5 звезд\" data-title-template=\"%s из 5 звезд\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/seemapabari\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/68a5b260e4129594327054324b494e15?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/68a5b260e4129594327054324b494e15?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/seemapabari\" class=\"reviewer-name\">seemapabari</a> <span class=\"review-date\">Июль 1, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">This is an easy to use plug in.  Problems do come up from time to time through search console and Google is not always clear about what we need to do to fix it.  The plug in support forum is very helpful and the team is really responsive.\n\nMy last error had to do with the logo missing in the theme appearance and Yoast plugin and James helped identify this quickly. I implemented the change as he recommended and the console error went away. \n\nHighly recommended. Our site gets lots of hits through AMP pages via mobile search so this plugin is very essential.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">cannot deactivate plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 из 5 звезд\" data-title-template=\"%s из 5 звезд\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				<a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/hiphauler\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/404cf628cecc92919fdab5141e7ecf3b?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/404cf628cecc92919fdab5141e7ecf3b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/hiphauler\" class=\"reviewer-name\">hiphauler</a> <span class=\"review-date\">Июнь 18, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Attempted to deactivate the plugin from Installed Plugins menu and it just hangs. Have to go through the backend and forcibly rip it out.</div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:53:\"Enable AMP on your WordPress site, the WordPress way.\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.1.2.2.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:12:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:89:\"Create great web experiences via AMP-powered websites or visually rich, engaging stories.\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:156:\"Story editor enables creation of pages in a horizontal, page-based interface, with background media, with blocks that can be dragged, rotated, and animated.\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:179:\"In the website experience, theme support enables you to reuse the active theme\'s templates and stylesheets; all WordPress features (menus, widgets, comments) are available in AMP.\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:191:\"All core themes are supported, but many themes can be served as AMP with minimal changes, Otherwise, behavior is often as if JavaScript is turned off in the browser since scripts are removed.\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:131:\"Reader mode templates are still available, but they are differ from the active theme, any validation errors are silently sanitized.\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:167:\"Switch from Reader mode to Transitional or Standard mode in AMP settings screen. You may need to disable the admin bar in AMP if your theme has a larger amount of CSS.\";}i:7;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:120:\"Make the entire site available in AMP or pick specific post types and templates; you can also opt-out on per-post basis.\";}i:8;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-8.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:149:\"Plugin checks for AMP validity and will indicate when either: no issues are found, new issues need moderation, or issues block AMP from being served.\";}i:9;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:56:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-9.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"The editor will surface validation issues during content authoring. The specific blocks with validation errors are indicated.\";}i:10;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-10.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:154:\"Validated URLs include the list of validation errors encountered, giving control over whether sanitization for a validation error is accepted or rejected.\";}i:11;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-11.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:143:\"Styles added by themes and plugins are automatically concatenated, minified, and tree-shaken to try to keep the total under 50KB of inline CSS.\";}i:12;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:57:\"https://ps.w.org/amp/assets/screenshot-12.png?rev=2108964\";s:7:\"caption\";s:125:\"A WP-CLI command is provided to check the URLs on a site for AMP validity. Results are available in the admin for inspection.\";}}s:8:\"versions\";a:27:{s:3:\"0.2\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.3\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.2.zip\";s:5:\"0.3.3\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.3.3.zip\";s:3:\"0.4\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.zip\";s:5:\"0.4.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.4.2\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.4.2.zip\";s:3:\"0.5\";s:50:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.5.zip\";s:5:\"0.5.1\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.5.1.zip\";s:5:\"0.6.0\";s:52:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/amp.0.6.0.zi